        <h2> king of hearts </h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Was born on the 16<sup>th</sup> of November in 1935</li>
            <li>At the age of 15, he entered the University of Cairo College of Medicine with a scholarship</li>
            <li>He was educated in Chicago, then moved to Britian in 1962 to work in the Chest Hospital in London.</li>
            <li> He obtained a fellowship from the Royal College of Surgenos in London,<br>and received titles and honors from the largest universities around the world  </li>
            <li>In 1983, he performed a heart transplant for an Englishman, to enter the Guinness Book of Records as the longest living person with a transplanted heart,<br> for a period of 33 years until the man died in 2016. </li>
        </ul> <hr>
